SPAIN DAYBOOK: Parliament Holds Wealth Tax Vote; Mortgage Loans

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-09-22T05:31:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/spain-daybook-parliament-holds-wealth-tax-vote-mortgage-loans.html
Spain ’s parliament is slated to
ratify a government decree to reintroduce a wealth tax.  WHAT TO WATCH:  *Spain’s National Energy Commission meets in Madrid.  *Finance Minister Elena Salgado travels to Washington to
participate in the G-20,  World Bank  and International Monetary
Fund meetings.  *Government Spokesman and Development Minister Jose Blanco
will be interviewed on the Telecinco channel at 9 a.m. CET.  ECONOMY:  *Spain’s National Statistics Institute will publish
mortgage loans data for July at 9 a.m. CET.  EQUITIES:  *CaixaBank will hold a board meeting in Barcelona.  *New shares in Abertis Infraestructuras SA start trading on
Spanish stock exchanges.  *Endesa SA had its long-term credit rating raised to A-from
BBB+ by Standard & Poor’s.  MARKETS:  *The  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  declined 1.8 percent to 8,210.30.  *The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing
costs widened to 363.5 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
